nested_items.name: StreamingDistributionList
nested_items.description: The StreamingDistributionList type.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: The value you provided for the Marker request parameter.

nested_items.name: NextMarker
nested_items.description: If IsTruncated is true, this element is present and contains the value you can use for the Marker request parameter to continue listing your RTMP distributions where they left off.

nested_items.name: MaxItems
nested_items.description: The value you provided for the MaxItems request parameter.

nested_items.name: IsTruncated
nested_items.description: A flag that indicates whether more streaming distributions remain to be listed. If your results were truncated, you can make a follow-up pagination request using the Marker request parameter to retrieve more distributions in the list.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of streaming distributions that were created by the current Amazon Web Services account.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains one StreamingDistributionSummary element for each distribution that was created by the current Amazon Web Services account.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The identifier for the distribution, for example, EDFDVBD632BHDS5.

nested_items.name: ARN
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) for the streaming distribution. For example: arn:aws:cloudfront::123456789012:streaming-distribution/EDFDVBD632BHDS5, where 123456789012 is your Amazon Web Services account ID.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: Indicates the current status of the distribution. When the status is Deployed, the distribution's information is fully propagated throughout the Amazon CloudFront system.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The date and time the distribution was last modified.

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: The domain name corresponding to the distribution, for example, d111111abcdef8.cloudfront.net.

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: The DNS name of the Amazon S3 origin.

nested_items.name: OriginAccessIdentity
nested_items.description: The CloudFront origin access identity to associate with the distribution. Use an origin access identity to configure the distribution so that end users can only access objects in an Amazon S3 bucket through CloudFront.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of CNAME aliases, if any, that you want to associate with this distribution.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains the CNAME aliases, if any, that you want to associate with this distribution.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: TrustedSigners
nested_items.description: A complex type that specifies the Amazon Web Services accounts, if any, that you want to allow to create signed URLs for private content. If you want to require signed URLs in requests for objects in the target origin that match the PathPattern for this cache behavior, specify true for Enabled, and specify the applicable values for Quantity and Items.If you don't want to require signed URLs in requests for objects that match PathPattern, specify false for Enabled and 0 for Quantity. Omit Items. To add, change, or remove one or more trusted signers, change Enabled to true (if it's currently false), change Quantity as applicable, and specify all of the trusted signers that you want to include in the updated distribution.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: This field is true if any of the Amazon Web Services accounts in the list are configured as trusted signers. If not, this field is false.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The number of Amazon Web Services accounts in the list.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: A list of Amazon Web Services account identifiers.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Comment
nested_items.description: The comment originally specified when this distribution was created.

nested_items.name: PriceClass
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information about price class for this streaming distribution.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: Whether the distribution is enabled to accept end user requests for content.
